OL,3,CInfected blood survivor demands: 'No
OL,4,Cmore platitudes, we need to hear
OL,5,Canswers'
OL,7,FIt's no exaggeration to say for many
OL,8,Fof the people affected by the infected
OL,9,Fblood scandal, Monday will be a
OL,10,Fdefining day in their lives.
OL,12,FThat's the day they are going to hear
OL,13,Fthe findings from Sir Brian
OL,14,FLangstaff's far-reaching review into
OL,15,Fhow thousands of people in the UK were
OL,16,Fgiven infected blood products.
OL,18,FMany of them, like Ros Cooper who I
OL,19,Fmet at her mother Juliet's home in ,
OL,20,Fhave been campaigning for the truth
OL,21,Ffor decades.
